        "contentUri": "coremedia://teaser/106865194",
        "label": null,
        "title": "Campers hide in tents as suspected foreign boat arrives at Qld tourist beach",
        "content": {
          "descriptor": {
            "type": "tagname",
            "key": "div",
            "props": {},
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "tagname",
                "key": "@@standfirst",
                "props": {},
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "The group allegedly came ashore from a boat at Pennefather Beach, a popular camping spot about 50 kilometres north of Weipa, in the early hours of Tuesday morning."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tagname",
                "key": "p",
                "props": {},
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Queensland Police Minister Dan Purdie said Queensland officers were assisting federal authorities."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tagname",
                "key": "p",
                "props": {},
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "\"What I've heard today is that the people have made it ashore and police are helping Border Force to detain those people,\" he said."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        "dates": {
          "firstPublished": "2026-07-01T02:23:41+00:00",
